ing up under-valued colors; and (3) some proposals that go unaccepted when they leave too little surplus for the responders, or when the targeted color is not especially attractive to them. Given the short horizon and fixed proposer order, players will often make straightforward, locally profitable trades rather than hold out for complex multi-step repositioning.",
